quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  7,142,"And We appointed for Moses thirty nights (of solitude), and added ten (more), and he completed the time appointed by his Lord for forty nights. And Moses said unto his brother Aaron, \"Act for me amongst my people, and do what is right, and follow not"
  7,143,"And when Moses came to Our appointment, and his Lord spoke unto him, he said, \"O my Lord! Show me Thyself, that I may look on Thee!\" Allah said, \"Thou canst not see Me; but look upon the mountain. If it remains steady in its place, you have"
  7,144,"He said, \"O Moses! Verily, I have chosen you over the people with My messages and My words. Take then what I have brought you, and be of the thankful"
  7,145,"And We wrote for him upon Tablets, admonitions, commanding and explaining everything, and said, \"Hold fast to them, and bid your people take the best course, made clear therein. I will show you the abode of those who work abominations"
  7,146,"I will turn from My revelations those who wrongfully magnify themselves with pride in the earth; and though they see every Sign, they shall not believe therein, and if they see the path of rectitude they shall not take it for their path; but if they see t"
  7,147,"But those who deny Our revelations (or Signs) and the meeting of the Hereafter, in vain are their works. Shall they be rewarded save for that which they have done"
  7,148,"And the people of Moses, after he had left them, chose (for worship) an image of a lowing calf (or one that seemed to low) made out of their ornaments. Did they not see that it could not speak to them or guide them in the path? They chose it and became wr"
  7,149,"But when they bit their hands (in realization and fear) and saw that they had gone astray, they said, \"Verily, if our Lord have not compassion on us and forgive us we shall surely be of those who are lost"
  7,150,"And when Moses returned unto his people angry and grieved, he said, \"Evil is it that which you have done after I had gone! Would you hasten on the judgment of your Lord?\". And he threw down the tablets and seized his brother by the (hair on his)"
  7,151,"Moses prayed, \"O Lord! Forgive my brother and me and let us enter into Thy mercy; for Thou art the most merciful of the merciful"
  7,152,"Verily, those who have taken to themselves a calf, there shall reach them wrath from their Lord, and abasement in the life of this world; for thus do we reward those who forge a lie"
  7,153,"But those who have done bad works, and then turn again after them and believe - verily, your Lord, thereafter, is Forgiving and Merciful"
  7,154,"And when Moses´ wrath calmed down he took up the Tables, in the inscription of which was guidance and mercy for those who fear their Lord"
  7,155,"And Moses chose from his people seventy men for Our appointment; and when the earthquake took them he prayed, \"O my Lord! Had you willed, you could have destroyed both them and me before this. Will Thou destroy us for what the fools amongst us have d"